code: Theme of the Image/Video__Event announcement/Election call/Candidate presentation_bin
Theme of the Image/Video__Negative imagery/Negative campaigning: The image/video portrays the political opponent in a negative light. This can happen through sharp criticism or with humor._bin

Theme of the Image/Video__Positive imagery/Acclaims: The image/video portrays past and future achievements of the party/government in a positive light. This includes drawing a positive balance, saying “thank you” to campaign helpers, or positively discussing political plans/goals._bin
Theme of the Image/Video__Symbolic image of person(s)/politician(s)/citizen(s) looking directly into the camera (classic campaign poster image)._bin

Theme of the Image/Video__Events/Landscape & city scenes: Unlike a symbolic image, people/politicians are doing something, moving, or working (e.g., groups such as politicians, refugees, farmers, protesters, police officers, etc.). Alternatively, a city or (natural) landscape is shown where something is happening (e.g., forest dieback, fire, or flooding, nuclear power plants or wind turbines)._bin
